Package com.kicas.rp.data.flagdata

Class LocationMeta

java.lang.Object
com.kicas.rp.data.flagdata.FlagMeta
com.kicas.rp.data.flagdata.LocationMeta
public class LocationMeta extends FlagMeta
Allows a minecraft location (including its world and rotation values) to be stored. Used for the respawn-location flag.

    • readMetaString

      public void readMetaString(String metaString)
      Updates this location meta based on the given string. Valid inputs include:
      • x y z
      • x y z world
      • x y z yaw pitch
      • x y z yaw pitch world
      If no world is provided, the parser will default to the overworld.
      Specified by:
      readMetaString in class FlagMeta
      Parameters:
      metaString - the metadata in string form.

    • toMetaString

      public String toMetaString()
      Converts this location meta to a string form. The resulting string will only contain the x, y, and z parts of this meta and each number will be truncated to three decimal points.
      Specified by:
      toMetaString in class FlagMeta
      Returns:
      this location meta in string form.
